JOHANNESBURG - Mobile network MTN said on Thursday it was concerned about the repercussions of violent attacks on foreign nationals in South Africa.In Nigeria, MTN s offices were vandalised in what is believed to be anti-xenophobic protests in the capital, Abuja.READ: #Foreignermarch to go aheadIt is believed equipment was stolen from the offices.The mobile company has pleaded with South Africans and foreign nationals to remain calm. eNCA